HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 928
By Lynn
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the Mt. Juliet High
School Golden Bears upon reaching the finals of
the TSSAA Division I bowling state
championship tournament.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly should salute those student athletes
who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true champions of
whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of lads is the Mt. Juliet High School Golden
Bears, whose members have proven themselves to be the fiercest of competitors and truly
worthy of admiration by finishing as a finalist in the TSSAA Division I state bowling
championship tournament while posting an excellent 23-2 season record; and
WHEREAS, entering the state tournament with a 21-1 record, the Golden Bears bested
Dobyns-Bennett 14-13 to emerge victorious in their quarterfinal match-up and then defeated
Tullahoma 20-7 in the semi-final round to reach the championship match; and
WHEREAS, the Golden Bears' superb performance would not have been possible
without the stellar leadership of their coaches and the unfailing support of their families, their
fans, and their community; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Mt. Juliet High School boys' bowling team epitomize all
that is good in today's student athletes, as they have achieved a premier level of success in
competition while exhibiting the highest degree of character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of
young men not only made possible an outstanding season but also surely bode well for their
future success; and
HJR0928
012975
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to acknowledge
and applaud the Mt. Juliet Golden Bears for their exemplary season on the lanes; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the members and coaches of the Mt. Juliet High
School Golden Bears upon reaching the finals of the TSSAA Division I bowling state
championship tournament, thus distinguishing themselves as the second best team in Division I,
and extend to them our best wishes for every continued success in all their future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
